  "notes": [
    {
      "type": "Other",
      "text": "The Action Form mapping in the demonstrative example disables the form's validate() method. The Struts bean: write tag automatically encodes special HTML characters, replacing a \u0026lt; with \"\u0026amp;lt;\" and a \u0026gt; with \"\u0026amp;gt;\". This action can be disabled by specifying filter=\"false\" as an attribute of the tag to disable specified JSP pages. However, being disabled makes these pages susceptible to cross-site scripting attacks. An attacker may be able to insert malicious scripts as user input to write to these JSP pages."
    }
  ]
